import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    airport_counts = data['origin'].value_counts() + data['destination'].value_counts()
    airport_counts = airport_counts.reset_index().rename(columns={'index': 'airport', 0: 'count'})
    
    chart = sns.barplot(x='airport', y='count', data=airport_counts)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('Which airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['date_only'] = data['date'].dt.date
    date_counts = data['date_only'].value_counts().reset_index()
    date_counts.columns = ['date', 'count']
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=date_counts)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
